<!--
  Canonical AndroidManifest extras for any AZT-suite PEER app.

  Sister apps symlink this file in alongside their other shared bits
  (azt_collab_client/, examples/, android/) and reference it from
  buildozer.spec:

      android.extra_manifest_xml = %(source.dir)s/manifest_extras.xml

  where manifest_extras.xml is the symlink to this file.

  Spliced at top-level under <manifest>, before <application>, by
  p4a's extra-manifest-xml mechanism (buildozer key:
  android.extra_manifest_xml). Only top-level elements belong here.

  The <queries> block is required on Android 11+: without it,
  PackageManager lookups can't see the standalone server APK
  (org.atoznback.aztcollab) due to package-visibility restrictions,
  so azt_collab_client.transports.android_cp.discover() reports the
  server as unavailable even when it's installed.

  Do NOT declare <permission> or <provider> here — both are owned by
  the server APK (azt-collab/server_apk/manifest_extras.xml +
  p4a_hook.py:_inject_aztcollab_provider). The <uses-permission> for
  AZT_COLLAB_ACCESS comes from each peer's `android.permissions` line
  in buildozer.spec, not from this file.
-->

<queries>
    <package android:name="org.atoznback.aztcollab" />
</queries>
